The victim was shot and killed opposite the Khayelitsha fire station on Friday. CAPE TOWN - Police are still on the lookout for suspects in connection with the murder of a Khayelitsha man. The victim was shot and killed opposite the Khayelitsha fire station on Friday. The motive for the killing is still unknown. The police's Frederick van Wyk said: “Circumstances surrounding the shooting incident opposite the fire station in Khayelitsha were a 39-year-old man was murdered is under investigation. Cases of murder and car-jacking have been opened for further investigation. No suspects have been arrested.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)